  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT345-kilavi">pakal vantoḻukuvāṉait tōḻi “irā vā” eṉṟatu. </p>


        <p xml:lang="en">The confidante saying “come at night” to the one who
          unexpectedly came at day. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT345">
          <l> iḻaiyaṇin tiyalvaruṅ koṭiñci neṭuntēr</l>
          <l> varaimaru ṇeṭumaṇaṟ ṟavirttuniṉ ṟacaiit</l>
          <l> taṅkiṉi rāyiṟ ṟavaṟō teyya</l>
          <l> taḻaitā ḻalku livaḷpulam pakalat</l>
          <l> tāḻai taiiya tayaṅkutiraik koṭuṅkaḻi</l>
          <l> yiḻumeṉa volikku māṅkaṭ</l>
          <l> perunīr vēliyeñ ciṟunal lūrē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>[Would it be] a mistake, then, <note place="foot"> Srin.'s proposal of taking <term xml:lang="ta"> teyya </term> as a particle of admonition makes sense also here (cf. KT 81.4). </note> if you stayed, <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> taṅkiṉir </term>: the perfective aspect expresses here once again the hypothetical character of the question. </note></l>
          <l rend="indent">restraining [and] bringing to a stop <note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">  niṉṟu acaii </term>: is this an intensifying (quasi-)synonym compound or is <term xml:lang="ta"> niṉṟu </term> to be understood as an adverb to <term xml:lang="ta"> acaii </term>?  </note>  by the sand [dune]</l>
          <l rend="indent8">long as a mountain</l>
          <l rend="indent">the long chariot with the handle, coming forward adorned</l>
          <l rend="indent8">with jewels, <note place="foot"> Why is the chariot <term xml:lang="ta">iḻai aṇintu? </term> </note> ,</l>
          <l>− in our little good village with the great water for a fence,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">there, where in the winding backwaters</l>
          <l rend="indent2">the glittering wave sounds sweetly, <note place="foot">Is the connotation of <term xml:lang="ta"> iḻum </term> "sweet" or rather "loud"? </note> close to  <note place="foot"> What is expressed by <term xml:lang="ta"> taiiya </term> here? </note> the Tāḻai tree,</l>
          <l rend="indent">so that loneliness may leave her with a hip hung with foliage?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
